div.p:
Again,
            this very thing is shown by the reasoning that the Apostle makes there.
            He says,
            there is no power except from God;
            but those things which are from God are ordained;
            therefore every power is ordained by divine ordinance:
            thus whoever resists the power resists God's ordinance;
            but whoever resists God's ordinance acquires damnation for himself:
            therefore etc.
